[DhtmlXQ_comment0]eg xqsycj tjm 002 1p1e pw 1a||||In this example, the pawn side has an extra ally in the form of an elephant. ||The mere addition of this elephant would dramatically change the outcome of this endgame. ||As the elephant is in the center of the board, it allow the red king to be mobile and thus control the important rib files, depending on how black responds. ||The elephant can be also used to make idle moves to force black's king to make undesierable plays. ||For red to win, the king must control one rib file  while the pawn must control the other rib file for the kill to materialize.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment5]Key move to winning!||Red targets and limits the movement of the black king with this move.[/DhtmlXQ_comment5]
